Read: Write-up on Domain Modeling

Read:

Read this write-up (Links to an external site.) on domain modeling.

Focus on reading slowly and carefully. While reading, type out and run all the code samples you come across. Do not copy and paste.

Reflect:

 Answer the following questions in your own words.

What's domain modeling?
Why are domain models so useful to programmers?
What's are some attributes and behaviors from a past job that you could model?
Considering a domain model of a library answer the following questions:
How would a book shelf relate to the rest of the objects in the library?
What methods might be included in the library domain?
What would might be the parent object of a book?
What could be considered a child object of a book?

After writing your reflection, you'll be able to read and reply to your classmates' reflections as well.